cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is focused on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically text classification and sequence labeling. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses reinforcement learning to automatically find shared architecture, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural architecture search (NAS), which is a popular topic in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since it deals with designing shared neural architecture.
